President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Raúl M. Arias-Marxuach as Circuit Judge on the United States Court of Appeals for the First Circuit. Arias-Marxuach is currently a Judge on the United States District Court for the District of Puerto Rico and previously worked as Vice Chair of the Litigation Practice Group at McConnell Valdés LLC. He has experience in commercial litigation and has served as a law clerk to Associate Justice Antonio S. Negrón-García of the Supreme Court of Puerto Rico. Arias-Marxuach holds a B.A. from Boston College, a J.D. from the University of Puerto Rico School of Law, and an L.L.M. from Harvard Law School.

Additionally, President Trump intends to nominate Maria Teresa B. Cenzon as Judge on the District Court of Guam. Cenzon currently serves as a Judge on the Superior Court of Guam, handling civil, criminal, domestic, and probate cases. Prior to her appointment to the bench, she worked as Chief Legal Counsel to the Governor of Guam and Director of Policy, Planning & Community Relations for the Unified Judiciary of Guam. Cenzon also has experience in private practice, advising large local and international corporations as well as government agencies. She obtained her B.A. from Marquette University and her J.D. from Loyola University-Chicago School of Law.